Countdown Timer with Tkinter:

A countdown timer program with a graphical user interface (GUI) built using Python and the Tkinter library. The user can specify a time in minutes and seconds, and the program will count down to zero, displaying the remaining time in a digital clock format.

Features:

Graphical user interface with Tkinter
Accepts user input for countdown time in minutes and seconds
Counts down to zero, displaying the remaining time in a digital clock format
Plays a sound when the countdown reaches zero
Allows the user to start, pause, resume, or reset the countdown
Displays the countdown status (running, paused, or finished)

Requirements:

Python 3.x
Tkinter library (usually comes pre-installed with Python)
